  "detailed_description": [
    {
      "heading": "Hot-Swappable Fan",
      "text": "The MikroTik MT-HotSwapFan is a backup hot-swappable cooling fan designed for MikroTik high-performance devices such as the CCR2216 and CRS518. It allows you to replace a faulty or worn fan without powering down the device, helping maintain continuous operation in mission-critical network environments. This is especially important in data centers, enterprise networks, and ISP installations where uptime and reliability are essential. The fan is engineered to provide stable airflow and efficient heat dissipation, ensuring optimal operating temperatures for demanding workloads."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Hot-Swappable Fan",
      "text": "With an estimated MTBF of approximately 100,000 hours at 25°C, the MT-HotSwapFan is designed for long-term, dependable performance. It is ideal as a spare or replacement fan to keep on hand for preventive maintenance or rapid service. Using original MikroTik replacement components ensures full compatibility, proper fit, and consistent cooling performance, helping extend the lifespan of your networking equipment while minimizing downtime and service interruptions."
    }
  ],
